for each complex number &quot;z&quot;. Let us define

:formula_46

Obviously, &quot;p*&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) ≠ 0 for all &quot;z&quot; in C. Consider the polynomial &quot;f&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) = &quot;p&quot;(&quot;z&quot;)&quot;p*&quot;(&quot;z&quot;). Then &quot;f&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) ≠ 0 for each &quot;z&quot; in C. Furthermore,

