* Weierstrass factorization theorem, a generalization of the theorem to other entire functions
*Eilenberg–Niven theorem, a generalization of the theorem to polynomials with quaternionic coefficients and variables
*Hilbert&#x27;s Nullstellensatz, a generalization to several variables of the assertion that complex roots exist
*Bézout&#x27;s theorem, a generalization to several variables of the assertion on the number of roots.

