== Conjugation, the norm, and reciprocal ==
Conjugation of quaternions is analogous to conjugation of complex numbers and to transposition (also known as reversal) of elements of Clifford algebras. To define it, let formula_26 be a quaternion. The conjugate of is the quaternion formula_27. It is denoted by , &quot;qt&quot;, formula_28, or . Conjugation is an involution, meaning that it is its own inverse, so conjugating an element twice returns the original element. The conjugate of a product of two quaternions is the product of the conjugates &quot;in the reverse order&quot;. That is, if and are quaternions, then , not .
